         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/3/87. ¶  ¶ If I do not write much, dear Mr Dyer, you will know, it is not from want of attachment to Kew, but by the force of overwhelming work. The "Key" is still far from completion, and daily du...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.03.16a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 220-1.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Stamped</seg> Royal Gardens Kew 2. May. 1887; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in ink by J. Baker</seg>: <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Selaginella</hi>
                     </seg> sent from Endeavour River [Coll.] Persieh is <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">[pron]iflora</hi>
                     </seg> Baker JGB, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and in pencil by W. Thiselton-Dye</seg>r And 4.5.87 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[letter not found].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>16/3/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I do not write much, dear Mr Dyer, you will know, it is not from want of attachment to Kew, but by the force of overwhelming work. The "Key" is still far from completion, and daily duties of routine are always heavy anyhow. Yesterday I gave evidence on "forests" before a parliamentary Commission.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 16 March 1887, p. 9, col. 6; see Frost &amp; S. Harvey (1997).</p>
               </note> Forest-affairs look very gloomy for the next century anywhere in readily accessible regions.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I greet with delight your Bulletin!<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The first part of Kew's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bulletin of miscellaneous information</seg> was published in January 1887.</p>
               </note> Some thing of the kind I had in contemplation, if I could have remained in the Garden. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prof Luerssen has only examined yet a small portion of the Papuan Ferns, so I have resolved, to send to Kew fragments of each species; from what little I have, only small pieces can be spared, as Sydney and Brisbane have also to be supplied. But to keep faith with Dr Luerssen I would beg of Mr Baker to communicate with him on any species which may perhaps prove new; — Mr Forbes ferns did not come here.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Red pencil line in margin against</seg> I would beg … proves new. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The initials </seg>JGB [John Gilbert Baker] <seg style="font-style: italic; ">are alongside the line</seg>.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See notes to M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 17 February 1886 (in this edition as 86-02-17a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Davidson, who went with Mr Sayer on a mission of mine to the summit of Mt Bellenden Ker,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
               </note> will, (if he does not alter his plans) return next month to England, where his father is the Proprietor of a Great Iron factory. The young Gentleman will bring you the small case with rooted plants of the redflowering <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>. Though<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Red pencil line in margin against</seg> will bring … though <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in lead pencil in margin </seg>Not yet rec 10-8-87 W.W. [William Watson] <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and</seg> Failed, see lett 4/7/87 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[i.e. M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 4 July 1887 (in this edition as 87-07-04a), which arrived at Kew on 22 August 1887].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> hardier than any other species, it should arrive in Spring at Kew. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It was Mr Findlay, after whom I named the Bertya Findlay[aea],<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>after whom … Findlay[aea] <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is a marginal note with intended position indicated by an asterisk. The end of the word is cramped at edge of sheet, but it is definitely not the correct Findlayi</seg>. </p>
               </note> who kindly got the cuttings for the second time and planted them in pots. So they came here, where they have been under my care for many month on the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">few square yards</hi>
               </seg> of garden-ground at my little Cottage.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">these</hi>
               </seg> particular cuttings will also show the brilliant color of the var cardinalis of C. speciosa, such as I saw when 1873<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1873 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">interlined</seg>.</p>
               </note> I discovered in one single valley the red flowered C. Lawrenciana. Speaking of the bid<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>bit?</p>
               </note> of ground on which I dwell, I am reminded of Seume's words </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">"Von allen diesen fetten Gaunen</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Gehöret mir ja nicht, </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">ein Fussbreit Land um Kohl darauf zu bauen,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Zu einem ländlichen Gericht."<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M is evidently quoting from memory, and somewhat misquoting, from 'Abschiedschreiben an Münchhausen' (1792) by Johann Gottfried Seume (1763-1810):</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.9299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Ich habe von den vielen fetten Gauen,</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.9299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Auch keinen Fuss, mir meinen Kohl zu bauen</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.9299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Zu einem ländlichen Gericht.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Which, if I may fuse<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M is using a figurative sense of an archaic meaning of 'fuse', namely 'to set out hastily' (OED). </p>
               </note> it in English language, might be [put]<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word obscured by binding.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">"Of all the rich and verdant tillage,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Not so much is my share, </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">To grow a single dish of cabbage,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">For a plain rural fare!"</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Davidson will give you if you like a verbal account of the dangers and toil to ascend Mt Bellenden Ker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Just had a glorious letter from Asa Gray<note xml:id="ftn13" type="footnote" n="13">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bertya%20Findlayaea">Bertya Findlayaea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Correa%20speciosa%20var%20cardinalis">Correa speciosa var cardinalis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
